First time here, and unfortunately, it was the worst customer service I’ve ever experienced — and I’m from LA.
The cashier looked completely over it, mind you it's 11am like she didn’t want to be there at all. (Very long eyelash extensions) didn't offer a receipt. They got my order wrong, and when I politely said, “Oh, it’s supposed to be a matcha!” I got no response. I waited, they called my name again with the correct order, I thanked them… and got a dry “Have a good day.”

If you’re going to have an open-concept space and be a morning spot, you need staff who can actually function in that setting.

The good: donuts are good, coffee too. Matcha isn’t amazing but still one of the better ones in Charlotte. Everything bagel is different — not bad, just different.

The weird: there was a person probably a manager standing between two visibly miserable employees who seemed to have beef with each other? Or maybe with the customers? Who knows. But if their job is to observe they should also correct when customer service is clearly lacking

All in all wouldn't patron again, the first experience left a bad taste in my mouth.
